The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 US spies killed 

 Peshawar, April 19 (Reuters): Pro-Taliban militants beheaded a Pakistani tribesman and shot dead an Afghan cab driver said to have been acting as US informers in Pakistans Waziristan tribal region, officials said today. 

 The slayings came two days after a tribesmans headless body was found with a note saying the victim was an American spy. 

 Russia Iran 

 Moscow (Reuters): Russia said on Wednesday it wanted to refrain from taking action before a UN deadline set for Tehran to halt uranium enrichment expired. 

 Danube fears 

 Bistret, Romania (Reuters): Thousands of Romanians fled their homes on Wednesday as the rising riverwater of the Danube flooded more than 100 villages and threatened to destroy many others. 




